01:10:10,875 --> 01:10:15,375
The five minute snooze ends up
being more than ten minutes!

1017
01:10:15,375 --> 01:10:17,750
Sorry.
- I know that feeling.

1018
01:10:20,625 --> 01:10:22,083
So why did you call me out here?

1019
01:10:22,208 --> 01:10:25,750
Naina, I need to tell you
something.

1020
01:10:30,417 --> 01:10:31,625
What?

1021
01:10:31,625 --> 01:10:35,125
After Biji's death I
realised something...

1022
01:10:36,792 --> 01:10:38,625
life is too short.

1023
01:10:40,417 --> 01:10:48,167
Everything is here and now...
the chances, the moments.

1024
01:10:49,833 --> 01:10:53,792
And a delay won't change the
facts.

1025
01:10:57,167 --> 01:11:04,292
Yes, but...
- Now I hope he understands
this.

1026
01:11:12,833 --> 01:11:16,167
What's up? Why did you call me
here?

1027
01:11:16,875 --> 01:11:21,667
Arjun... don't postpone the
wedding.

1028
01:11:23,292 --> 01:11:27,417
Have you lost it completely?
At this moment?

1029
01:11:27,417 --> 01:11:29,083
Naina...I mean..

1030
01:11:29,250 --> 01:11:30,750
Listen to me, Arjun.

1031
01:11:31,583 --> 01:11:34,542
Do you think Biji would like
it if you postponed the wedding?

1032
01:11:35,042 --> 01:11:37,250
Of course not, never!

1033
01:11:38,000 --> 01:11:40,250
Biji always told us
that life is very short.

1034
01:11:40,250 --> 01:11:43,417
And that we should
celebrate every day...

1035
01:11:43,417 --> 01:11:49,792
..every relationship, the
love we share, our friends.

1036
01:11:50,958 --> 01:11:52,833
And this is your wedding!

1037
01:11:56,083 --> 01:11:58,292
She was so excited and happy..

1038
01:11:59,542 --> 01:12:01,958
..that you and Gayatri
were getting married.

1039
01:12:02,458 --> 01:12:04,583
Here... now...

1040
01:12:07,083 --> 01:12:08,583
I know it's tough, brother
but...

1041
01:12:08,667 --> 01:12:10,000
God knows I know.

1042
01:12:10,750 --> 01:12:12,458
Biji is with us.

1043
01:12:15,583 --> 01:12:20,167
She is here and she will always
be!

1044
01:12:20,333 --> 01:12:22,167
Make sure she is happy.

1045
01:12:24,292 --> 01:12:26,458
You know this is the
generosity and love of our
elders...

1046
01:12:27,667 --> 01:12:32,500
..even as they leave us
they expect us to be happy.

1047
01:12:38,667 --> 01:12:44,625
Do you remember in school I
always failed in English
spelling...

1048
01:12:45,625 --> 01:12:50,333
Biji would teach me...
after learning it herself.

1049
01:12:52,250 --> 01:12:54,167
But she always got it wrong.

1050
01:12:56,625 --> 01:13:00,667
I got Gayatri to meet
her before anyone else.

1051
01:13:01,792 --> 01:13:03,958
Without her how can I...

1052
01:13:05,625 --> 01:13:09,625
Exactly the
way she would want you to.

1053
01:13:11,458 --> 01:13:12,875
Happy and smiling.

1054
01:13:16,583 --> 01:13:17,833
Go and talk to Gayatri.

1055
01:13:17,833 --> 01:13:25,125
"Why do we meet when we
have to lose each other?"

1056
01:13:25,125 --> 01:13:32,500
"When heart has to wither,
why does it blossom?"

1057
01:13:32,500 --> 01:13:39,833
"Why do we meet when we
have to lose each other?"

1058
01:13:39,833 --> 01:13:46,083
"When heart has to wither,
why does it blossom?"

1059
01:13:46,083 --> 01:13:47,708
I'm so glad you did that.

1060
01:13:47,917 --> 01:13:52,125
Anything for Biji, Naina.
Her happiness is in this.

1061
01:13:55,333 --> 01:13:57,083
Why did you ask me to be here?

1062
01:13:57,667 --> 01:14:01,625
You know what it is to lose a
loved one and still carry on.

1063
01:14:02,917 --> 01:14:09,917
And I felt that if you are with
me,
I wouldn't be all alone...

1064
01:14:13,875 --> 01:14:18,000
Well actually...
- I know.

1065
01:14:20,167 --> 01:14:21,542
But I promise

1066
01:14:22,792 --> 01:14:27,042
whenever you need me...

1067
01:14:27,958 --> 01:14:30,167
..no matter what... if you need
me...

1068
01:14:32,167 --> 01:14:33,542
I'll be there...

1069
01:14:34,708 --> 01:14:38,500
silent but strong.

1070
01:14:39,750 --> 01:14:41,125
Sure?

1071
01:14:41,667 --> 01:14:43,250
Sure!

1072
01:14:56,125 --> 01:15:03,458
"Lord is the savior."

1073
01:15:04,000 --> 01:15:08,875
"Lord is the savior."

1074
01:15:10,667 --> 01:15:18,708
"Lord is the savior."

1075
01:15:26,125 --> 01:15:33,042
"Lord is the savior."

1076
01:15:33,167 --> 01:15:38,583
"Lord is the savior."

1077
01:15:41,708 --> 01:15:50,333
"Lord is the savior."

1078
01:15:58,917 --> 01:16:04,292
"Lord is the savior."

1079
01:16:08,625 --> 01:16:10,000
Bye guys...

1080
01:16:10,708 --> 01:16:12,083
Bye.
- See you.

1081
01:16:12,250 --> 01:16:14,125
See you.
- Bye. See you.

1082
01:16:14,250 --> 01:16:15,625
Bye, Naina!
- See you. - Bye.

1083
01:16:15,792 --> 01:16:18,042
Shall we go?

1084
01:16:19,208 --> 01:16:22,917
Glad you made it. For a moment
I thought you're not coming.

1085
01:16:26,583 --> 01:16:27,792
Dhruv...

1086
01:16:27,792 --> 01:16:29,875
Take care, buddy.
- You too.

1087
01:16:30,875 --> 01:16:32,417
Congratulations.
- Thank you.

1088
01:16:32,417 --> 01:16:34,000
I'll get our bags.
- Yeah.

1089
01:16:47,708 --> 01:16:51,083
- Bye Jai. - Bye Naina.

1090
01:16:51,083 --> 01:16:52,917
If you ever visit Bombay...

1091
01:16:54,417 --> 01:16:55,792
Sure.

1092
01:17:56,208 --> 01:18:01,500
Dude, what's wrong with you?
Come on... cheers!

1093
01:18:01,625 --> 01:18:03,667
Cheers? For what?

1094
01:18:05,000 --> 01:18:08,125
Because we are free again!

1095
01:18:10,917 --> 01:18:15,708
Tell me, how was lunch?
And your mom?

1096
01:18:15,708 --> 01:18:17,042
Lunch.

1097
01:18:19,583 --> 01:18:23,333
It's too close to the kitchen,
do you have anything else?

1098
01:18:23,333 --> 01:18:26,542
This is too small, do
you have anything else?

1099
01:18:29,375 --> 01:18:30,875
I think this is fine.

1100
01:18:36,750 --> 01:18:38,083
Thank you.

1101
01:18:38,875 --> 01:18:40,792
What would you like to have,
aunty-ji? Some soup?

1102
01:18:40,792 --> 01:18:43,875
I'll have anything you call
for.
Your taste is the best.

1103
01:18:43,875 --> 01:18:45,333
Okay, no soup then.

1104
01:18:46,667 --> 01:18:52,000
One steam wantons without sauce
and a vegetarian noodles.

1105
01:18:52,000 --> 01:18:56,917
I don't like onions, carrots
and
mushrooms, so only add capsicum.

1106
01:18:56,917 --> 01:18:58,500
Yes ma'am.

1107
01:18:58,500 --> 01:19:00,417
What's up with you? Why so
silent?

1108
01:19:00,417 --> 01:19:03,083
China Garden is your
favourite restaurant.

1109
01:19:03,083 --> 01:19:09,292
Yes, mom, it is my favourite
but
Radhika is talking right now.

1110
01:19:09,417 --> 01:19:14,250
Idiot! Have you thought
about your wedding yet?

1111
01:19:14,250 --> 01:19:15,583
Come on, mom!

1112
01:19:16,250 --> 01:19:17,917
- Excuse me! - Yes?

1113
01:19:17,917 --> 01:19:20,875
Can I have one pepsi
with lots of ice. - Sure, sir.

1114
01:19:20,875 --> 01:19:22,208
Not aerated drinks again!

1115
01:19:22,208 --> 01:19:25,708
Excuse me, can you make
that an ice tea, please? Thank
you.

1116
01:19:25,708 --> 01:19:27,208
- And excuse me...
- Yes ma'am?

1117
01:19:27,292 --> 01:19:30,458
Please see to it that the food
is
very fresh and piping hot.

1118
01:19:30,458 --> 01:19:31,833
Sure ma'am.

1119
01:19:31,833 --> 01:19:35,958
And really hot! If it's not
hot, I won't accept it.

1120
01:19:35,958 --> 01:19:41,083
Excuse me, can you ask the
chef to use less ajinomoto?

1121
01:19:41,083 --> 01:19:45,083
Lunch! It ruined everything.

1122
01:19:45,083 --> 01:19:47,125
Any more questions, Mr. Govind?

1123
01:19:47,417 --> 01:19:51,458
No... so which restaurant was
this?

1124
01:19:52,292 --> 01:19:54,208
Govind... let's go
back to Chandigarh.

1125
01:19:54,208 --> 01:19:55,792
I can't get the wedding
out of my mind.

1126
01:19:55,792 --> 01:19:58,625
What are we doing here...
I mean what are we doing?

1127
01:19:59,583 --> 01:20:01,708
Bro, that wedding is over.

1128
01:20:02,333 --> 01:20:04,750
But more weddings will
happen I am sure.

1129
01:20:06,250 --> 01:20:08,583
But are you sure you can't get
the wedding out of your mind...

1130
01:20:08,583 --> 01:20:10,625
or is it 'someone' on your mind?

1131
01:20:13,458 --> 01:20:14,708
Do you think so?

1132
01:20:14,708 --> 01:20:16,042
I think so!

1133
01:20:19,042 --> 01:20:20,250
You know who?

1134
01:20:20,250 --> 01:20:21,542
You think I am stupid?

1135
01:20:21,542 --> 01:20:25,208
I know who! You want to know?

1136
01:20:25,667 --> 01:20:27,000
No!

1137
01:20:30,958 --> 01:20:34,208
So Jai is the guy from Delhi.

1138
01:20:34,833 --> 01:20:36,125
Stop it, Ritu!

1139
01:20:36,125 --> 01:20:37,583
I should stop it?

1140
01:20:39,250 --> 01:20:40,583
Okay.

1141
01:20:46,292 --> 01:20:52,542
I think you have a crush...
a little crush on him.

1142
01:20:54,167 --> 01:20:57,583
Dhruv still exists, you know.
He hasn't vanished.

1143
01:20:57,917 --> 01:21:04,500
Of course, that will be too
much to
ask. - Rubbish. You naughty girl.

1144
01:21:05,542 --> 01:21:08,708
Stop imagining things, Ritu.
The wedding is over.

1145
01:21:08,708 --> 01:21:14,208
I am back to my old routine and
he is back to his fun routine.

1146
01:21:23,208 --> 01:21:25,417
What were you saying, Jai?

1147
01:21:29,500 --> 01:21:33,417
Just a second...coaster..

1148
01:21:36,458 --> 01:21:38,125
..carry on.

1149
01:21:38,375 --> 01:21:40,583
Radhika, this isn't working.

1150
01:21:41,250 --> 01:21:44,625
What's wrong now? You want
to quit your job again!

1151
01:21:44,625 --> 01:21:47,125
No, this is not working.

1152
01:21:47,500 --> 01:21:49,833
You are frustrating me again.
What is 'this'?

1153
01:21:49,833 --> 01:21:51,625
This means us.

1154
01:21:54,167 --> 01:21:59,167
I am sorry. I know it's
coming like a surprise.

1155
01:21:59,417 --> 01:22:01,167
Why are we even together,
Radhika?

1156
01:22:01,167 --> 01:22:03,542
Because we want to get married,
Jai.

1157
01:22:03,542 --> 01:22:07,208
You want to get married or
do you want to marry me?

1158
01:22:07,208 --> 01:22:09,875
I don't understand... what
sort of question is that?

1159
01:22:09,875 --> 01:22:14,417
It may sound complicated but
it really is very simple.

1160
01:22:17,083 --> 01:22:18,250
At Arjun's wedding..

1161
01:22:18,250 --> 01:22:22,500
..I realised that though we are
together we really are far
apart.

1162
01:22:23,167 --> 01:22:25,208
It's because our priorities
are different.

1163
01:22:25,708 --> 01:22:27,042
Tell me..

1164
01:22:28,667 --> 01:22:29,875
..when was the last time..

1165
01:22:29,875 --> 01:22:32,375
..we really did something
together from our heart.

1166
01:22:34,792 --> 01:22:36,542
I just want to be honest..

1167
01:22:39,083 --> 01:22:40,417
.. that's it.

1168
01:22:41,833 --> 01:22:43,875
What are you getting at, Jai?

1169
01:22:44,167 --> 01:22:45,333
You mean the two years that...

1170
01:22:45,333 --> 01:22:49,083
I have invested into this
relationship are a waste?

1171
01:22:49,083 --> 01:22:51,500
Keeping track of your
21 family members'..

1172
01:22:51,500 --> 01:22:55,917
..21 birthdates and wishing
them is a waste?

1173
01:22:56,208 --> 01:22:59,458
Tolerating your annoying
habits is a waste?

1174
01:22:59,458 --> 01:23:03,375
Jai, to be honest, you are
ruining
my well laid out plan!

1175
01:23:04,750 --> 01:23:08,292
In the next two years I wanted
to have my first child...

1176
01:23:08,542 --> 01:23:09,792
now how's that going to happen?

1177
01:23:09,792 --> 01:23:13,417
Radhika, relax... calm down.

1178
01:23:13,750 --> 01:23:15,875
Probably the plan itself is
wrong.

1179
01:23:15,875 --> 01:23:20,458
I mean somewhere along the way
the plans scored over love.

1180
01:23:20,458 --> 01:23:25,333
But who knows... right? Perhaps
there's someone else for us...

1181
01:23:25,667 --> 01:23:30,125
Who will love us...
for the real reasons.

1182
01:23:30,875 --> 01:23:32,250
The right reason.

1183
01:23:32,250 --> 01:23:37,417
Someone else? You met someone
else?

1184
01:23:40,833 --> 01:23:42,167
I did!

1185
01:23:51,250 --> 01:23:54,708
But neither am I with her nor
is she madly in love with me.

1186
01:23:54,708 --> 01:23:56,083
There's no such thing like that.

1187
01:23:56,583 --> 01:23:59,250
She has nothing to do with
our situation.

1188
01:24:02,500 --> 01:24:03,833
I swear!

1189
01:24:05,708 --> 01:24:07,125
Have you told your mom?

1190
01:24:07,917 --> 01:24:10,458
She is sure to kill me!

1191
01:24:11,917 --> 01:24:19,375
I was hoping you could
break the news to her.

1192
01:24:32,042 --> 01:24:33,375
Coaster!

1193
01:24:35,042 --> 01:24:36,583
I guess you are right.

1194
01:24:37,833 --> 01:24:41,958
I mean, I am the strong type
but...

1195
01:24:42,083 --> 01:24:49,458
I thought something like
this would shatter me.

1196
01:24:50,333 --> 01:24:51,667
But I'm not.

1197
01:24:52,875 --> 01:24:54,333
Isn't that strange?

1198
01:25:00,917 --> 01:25:07,625
We could remain friends... I
mean,
if it's alright with you.

1199
01:25:08,208 --> 01:25:12,917
I need some time, Jai.
I'll call you.

1200
01:25:14,583 --> 01:25:15,917
Okay.

1201
01:25:21,500 --> 01:25:22,833
Jai..

1202
01:25:25,708 --> 01:25:32,042
.. if ever wish to pursue
the girl you've met...

1203
01:25:32,250 --> 01:25:35,708
please do it after you've
changed your habits.

1204
01:25:36,625 --> 01:25:38,000
It will create a good
impression.

1205
01:25:44,792 --> 01:25:47,750
- Hello. - Hi, busy?

1206
01:25:48,667 --> 01:25:51,083
Just working for the exhibition.

1207
01:25:51,083 --> 01:25:53,083
Any plans for tonight?

1208
01:25:53,083 --> 01:25:56,875
Just me and Arundhati Roy...
at the most some coffee.

1209
01:25:56,875 --> 01:26:00,250
That sounds exciting.

1210
01:26:00,458 --> 01:26:01,833
Don't rub it in!

1211
01:26:01,917 --> 01:26:05,250
I'll have you know, though I
may
not agree with her viewpoint but...

1212
01:26:05,250 --> 01:26:07,333
she is way more interesting
than ..

1213
01:26:07,333 --> 01:26:10,250
..your financial spreadsheets
and numbers...

1214
01:26:10,250 --> 01:26:13,125
with whom you spend every night.

1215
01:26:13,292 --> 01:26:16,792
Fine, let's change our plans.

1216
01:26:16,875 --> 01:26:18,208
Dinner.

1217
01:26:18,292 --> 01:26:21,875
Wow, sounds good.

1218
01:26:22,000 --> 01:26:27,375
- Tonight at 9pm. Don't be
late.
- Okay bye.

1219
01:26:39,083 --> 01:26:42,458
Weren't you afraid of her?
That was quite a risk.

1220
01:26:43,125 --> 01:26:48,375
I sure was but I figured that
it
makes sense to accept the truth.

1221
01:26:48,375 --> 01:26:54,500
As for risk, crossing the road
is also a risk. Isn't it?

1222
01:26:54,500 --> 01:26:57,083
Well that was it!

1223
01:26:57,708 --> 01:27:03,208
So Mr. Govind, now you and
I are in the same category.

1224
01:27:03,208 --> 01:27:07,167
Single... and officially
ready to mingle.

1225
01:27:07,167 --> 01:27:09,125
No, brother.

1226
01:27:09,125 --> 01:27:11,417
I don't belong to that
category anymore.

1227
01:27:12,167 --> 01:27:13,417
You know Sheila?

1228
01:27:13,417 --> 01:27:15,083
Sheila? God damn it Govind!

1229
01:27:15,083 --> 01:27:19,375
We are back in Delhi...
back to reality.

1230
01:27:19,583 --> 01:27:21,167
You took her number?

1231
01:27:24,583 --> 01:27:27,917
You basket, when?

1232
01:27:27,917 --> 01:27:29,250
What are you doing?

1233
01:27:29,875 --> 01:27:31,833
Come on bro, it's simple
technology!

1234
01:27:31,833 --> 01:27:34,583
FB... friend request.

1235
01:27:35,375 --> 01:27:38,958
I think I'll ask her
out for coffee today.

1236
01:27:38,958 --> 01:27:42,125
I think you should take
your sad story elsewhere.

1237
01:27:42,125 --> 01:27:43,417
I'm committed, man!

1238
01:27:43,417 --> 01:27:45,458
Committed my ass!

1239
01:27:45,458 --> 01:27:46,958
Being committed to the
idea of commitment..

1240
01:27:46,958 --> 01:27:48,292
.. doesn't mean you are
committed.

1241
01:27:48,958 --> 01:27:50,750
Have you lost it completely?
- Get lost.

1242
01:27:50,750 --> 01:27:52,917
Sheila? Facebook?

1243
01:27:52,917 --> 01:27:54,250
Loser.
- Give me a break!

1244
01:27:55,667 --> 01:27:57,375
Oh shit! Naina!

1245
01:28:01,583 --> 01:28:07,083
Hey Jai, how are you? Please
accept my friend request.

1246
01:28:07,083 --> 01:28:10,208
I want to tag you in
the wedding pictures.

1247
01:28:10,208 --> 01:28:13,208
Bye! Smileys!

1248
01:28:13,333 --> 01:28:16,750
Don't be silly! We were
all there at the wedding.

1249
01:28:16,750 --> 01:28:19,083
She wants to share the
pictures,
that's it.

1250
01:28:19,333 --> 01:28:21,542
Even I was there at the
wedding...

1251
01:28:21,708 --> 01:28:23,875
but nobody's sharing
anything with me.

1252
01:28:23,875 --> 01:28:27,000
Well Sheila is sharing...
her old age.

1253
01:28:29,458 --> 01:28:32,333
That was a good one. Let's
see the pictures.

1254
01:28:33,417 --> 01:28:38,125
Hey check out pinku... and
Gayatri!

1255
01:28:43,083 --> 01:28:44,417
Look at Arjun!

1256
01:28:46,417 --> 01:28:47,750
What now?

1257
01:28:48,000 --> 01:28:50,417
Now... back to work!

1258
01:28:51,125 --> 01:28:53,750
You like Naina, right?

1259
01:28:54,708 --> 01:28:59,625
Govind! Naina is with Dhruv
and she lives in Bombay.

1260
01:28:59,625 --> 01:29:00,958
Where do we live?

1261
01:29:01,250 --> 01:29:04,625
Jai.

1262
01:29:04,917 --> 01:29:07,292
Jai, we need to renew these
advertisement contracts.

1263
01:29:07,500 --> 01:29:10,083
Didn't you close the
endorsements
deal last time?

1264
01:29:10,083 --> 01:29:11,958
- Yes sir.
- Good!

1265
01:29:11,958 --> 01:29:14,667
So get ready, this time
you're going to Bombay.

1266
01:29:14,792 --> 01:29:16,792
- Here's the file. - Okay, sir.

1267
01:29:20,875 --> 01:29:23,125
Let's book your ticket.

1268
01:29:38,750 --> 01:29:40,333
- Hi... - Hello.

1269
01:29:40,833 --> 01:29:44,208
- Come... - Thank you.

1270
01:29:49,667 --> 01:29:54,375
So, I've ordered some wine.
The one you like?

1271
01:30:01,792 --> 01:30:03,125
Well done.

1272
01:30:05,458 --> 01:30:07,917
So, a dinner plan...
out of the blue?

1273
01:30:09,000 --> 01:30:12,208
Well, it has been a while..

1274
01:30:15,625 --> 01:30:17,250
..and there's something else.

1275
01:30:18,375 --> 01:30:19,708
What?

1276
01:30:21,583 --> 01:30:24,375
I'm leaving for Singapore
tomorrow for ten days.

1277
01:30:27,750 --> 01:30:32,083
- Great! - What?

1278
01:30:32,083 --> 01:30:34,792
That means you will
miss my exhibition.

1279
01:30:35,417 --> 01:30:38,750
Oh God! How could I forget!

1280
01:30:38,750 --> 01:30:41,625
I am so sorry... I feel so
stupid!

1281
01:30:41,625 --> 01:30:44,417
I have a very good reason for
it.

1282
01:30:47,500 --> 01:30:48,792
Go on!

1283
01:30:49,042 --> 01:30:54,917
The management thinks if I like
the set-up over there...

1284
01:30:54,917 --> 01:30:58,792
I could be the Vice President
for Emerging Markets.

1285
01:30:58,792 --> 01:31:00,417
Isn't that great?

1286
01:31:02,875 --> 01:31:06,333
That's great, Dhruv. I
am so happy for you.

1287
01:31:06,625 --> 01:31:10,500
You always wanted this.
- Thanks.

1288
01:31:12,167 --> 01:31:15,333
Don't worry about the
exhibition, really!

1289
01:31:23,333 --> 01:31:24,667
Will you marry me?

1290
01:31:28,542 --> 01:31:31,625
Your menu.
- Sir? - Thanks!

1291
01:31:31,625 --> 01:31:34,167
- Give us a few minutes? - Sure
sir.

1292
01:31:37,333 --> 01:31:43,750
Listen... I know that
everything
is happening very quickly.

1293
01:31:43,750 --> 01:31:46,667
But that's exactly how life
throws up opportunities.

1294
01:31:47,042 --> 01:31:50,792
I'll be back in ten days and
then you can decide...

1295
01:31:50,792 --> 01:31:55,292
the type of wedding, the
location,
the setting.

1296
01:31:56,250 --> 01:31:57,583
Toast?

1297
01:31:58,417 --> 01:31:59,750
Come on...

1298
01:32:03,875 --> 01:32:07,708
the future is about to unfold
with unexpected surprises.

1299
01:32:07,708 --> 01:32:09,000
Trust me.

1300
01:32:16,375 --> 01:32:20,083
Good morning, sir.
Have a pleasant flight.

1301
01:32:33,250 --> 01:32:34,833
Well, well... what could
have made my super..

1302
01:32:34,833 --> 01:32:37,708
..independent daughter
think of her mother?

1303
01:32:38,958 --> 01:32:40,417
Dhruv proposed to me.

1304
01:32:41,167 --> 01:32:44,417
He did? What did you reply?

1305
01:32:45,583 --> 01:32:46,917
Nothing.

1306
01:32:47,792 --> 01:32:49,125
What do you mean nothing?

1307
01:32:51,625 --> 01:32:53,958
He left no room for me to reply.

1308
01:32:54,417 --> 01:32:57,292
He was so sure I would
say yes that...

1309
01:32:57,750 --> 01:33:00,958
he didn't realise whether
I had said yes or no.

1310
01:33:02,750 --> 01:33:06,500
What's the matter, dear?
Aren't you happy?

1311
01:33:07,458 --> 01:33:08,792
I don't know, mom.

1312
01:33:09,375 --> 01:33:16,958
You know Dhruv and I have
been good friends.

1313
01:33:17,833 --> 01:33:22,375
I'm an emotional fool while
he is too practical.

1314
01:33:22,375 --> 01:33:27,208
I believed this would be a
good combination for us.

1315
01:33:27,208 --> 01:33:30,917
And that he would bring a sense
of balance to my life.

1316
01:33:33,542 --> 01:33:34,875
But now you know...

1317
01:33:36,417 --> 01:33:39,542
How did you know, mom...
that dad was the one?

1318
01:33:40,625 --> 01:33:42,458
Or uncle Ashu after him?

1319
01:33:43,292 --> 01:33:44,625
A sign, Naina.

1320
01:33:45,375 --> 01:33:48,958
A little sign and you will know
it.

1321
01:33:48,958 --> 01:33:50,708
You will feel him...

1322
01:33:51,000 --> 01:33:57,625
you'll feel that thrill that
just fills up your heart.

1323
01:33:58,125 --> 01:34:03,083
Mom, hold on a second. Hello?

1324
01:34:03,083 --> 01:34:05,458
If you ever visit Bombay...

1325
01:34:05,458 --> 01:34:08,708
- Jai! - Hi Naina.

1326
01:34:09,042 --> 01:34:11,125
Listen, I am going to call you
back!

1327
01:34:12,292 --> 01:34:14,292
Yeah, sure.

1328
01:34:14,417 --> 01:34:15,750
Bye!

1329
01:34:18,333 --> 01:34:19,667
Mom...

1330
01:34:21,833 --> 01:34:23,167
Idiot!

1331
01:34:23,542 --> 01:34:26,125
Call as soon as you land...

1332
01:34:26,375 --> 01:34:29,333
on the advice of a
two-time divorcee!

1333
01:34:29,583 --> 01:34:32,667
Jai... you are... fantastic!

1334
01:34:32,667 --> 01:34:37,542
Naina, just do what you've
always done in life.

1335
01:34:37,542 --> 01:34:40,417
Follow you heart, not your mind.

1336
01:34:40,417 --> 01:34:41,750
Trust yourself.

1337
01:34:42,583 --> 01:34:46,500
I know you will take
the right decision.

1338
01:34:46,500 --> 01:34:47,750
Love you, sweetheart.

1339
01:34:47,750 --> 01:34:51,083
I love you too, mom. Bye!

1340
01:34:59,375 --> 01:35:03,167
Jai... what are you doing in
Bombay?

1341
01:35:03,167 --> 01:35:05,792
Well... I thought I'd visit you.

1342
01:35:07,542 --> 01:35:09,000
Just kidding!

1343
01:35:10,292 --> 01:35:12,500
Work brought me here so I
thought

1344
01:35:12,500 --> 01:35:15,333
you could show me around Bombay.

1345
01:35:15,333 --> 01:35:16,958
I'm so bored here at
this guest house.

1346
01:35:17,083 --> 01:35:19,375
Your timing couldn't
have been better!

1347
01:35:19,375 --> 01:35:24,458
Really? My dad always
said my timing sucked.

1348
01:35:24,583 --> 01:35:25,792
How is that?

1349
01:35:25,792 --> 01:35:29,375
Well... my arrival into this
world
put an end to his honeymoon period!

1350
01:35:31,708 --> 01:35:35,125
Nothing has changed neither
you nor your sad jokes!

1351
01:35:35,417 --> 01:35:37,833
Please... before they
get any sadder..

1352
01:35:37,958 --> 01:35:40,833
- Coffee? - Yeah!

1353
01:35:43,417 --> 01:35:44,750
Thank you.
- Welcome, ma'am.

1354
01:35:44,958 --> 01:35:46,708
So, now your exhibition is
set...

1355
01:35:46,708 --> 01:35:48,042
anything else that's exciting?

1356
01:35:48,542 --> 01:35:51,250
Nothing actually. You know..

1357
01:35:52,708 --> 01:35:58,208
Gayatri's wedding was so high
on energy... You were there. -
Yes.

1358
01:35:59,125 --> 01:36:01,833
that now everything seems
lifeless.

1359
01:36:01,833 --> 01:36:03,167
I really get it.

1360
01:36:03,292 --> 01:36:05,833
I still sing those songs
in the shower and...

1361
01:36:05,833 --> 01:36:09,125
my mom thinks it's
a sign. Ridiculous!

1362
01:36:09,125 --> 01:36:13,417
Maybe it is! Is Radhika ready?

1363
01:36:13,917 --> 01:36:15,292
Not anymore.

1364
01:36:17,167 --> 01:36:20,500
We... we broke up.

1365
01:36:22,292 --> 01:36:23,542
But, why?

1366
01:36:23,542 --> 01:36:26,667
I've figured out a slightly
more perfect option, Naina.

1367
01:36:28,833 --> 01:36:30,167
Being single!

1368
01:36:31,917 --> 01:36:34,417
And to be honest, Radhika
and my future had..

1369
01:36:34,417 --> 01:36:36,208
..a question mark dangling over
it.

1370
01:36:36,292 --> 01:36:40,000
But my mom hasn't given up hope.

1371
01:36:40,000 --> 01:36:42,292
- You know how they are. - I
know.

1372
01:36:42,542 --> 01:36:44,958
I guess all mothers are
like that.

1373
01:36:47,000 --> 01:36:48,458
How is Govind?

1374
01:36:50,000 --> 01:36:55,708
Govind... he got himself into
an interesting situation.

1375
01:36:56,500 --> 01:36:59,042
Really? You mean, Sheila?

1376
01:36:59,375 --> 01:37:00,750
So what? A slap?

1377
01:37:00,750 --> 01:37:03,792
Not exactly...

1378
01:37:07,542 --> 01:37:09,167
Hello sir.

1379
01:37:09,833 --> 01:37:13,292
- Salesman?
- No, sir.

1380
01:37:13,292 --> 01:37:16,667
- Bank account?
- No, sir.

1381
01:37:23,542 --> 01:37:28,625
Sir, I am Govind, Sheila's
friend.
I'm not a salesman.

1382
01:37:29,750 --> 01:37:32,167
- You are Sheila's friend?
- Yes, sir.

1383
01:37:33,875 --> 01:37:37,792
- Well... in that case, come
in.
- Thank you, sir.

1384
01:37:42,750 --> 01:37:44,667
- Would you like some tea?
- Yes.

1385
01:37:48,000 --> 01:37:49,792
Vinod, a cup of tea, please.

1386
01:37:55,333 --> 01:37:56,667
What?

1387
01:37:58,000 --> 01:37:59,333
Nothing, sir.

1388
01:37:59,792 --> 01:38:01,083
Sit down.

1389
01:38:02,542 --> 01:38:03,792
Can I clean my gun?

1390
01:38:03,792 --> 01:38:05,417
Oh... yes, please.

1391
01:38:07,958 --> 01:38:09,542
How did you and Sheila meet?

1392
01:38:09,542 --> 01:38:14,208
We met at Arjun and
Gayatri's wedding.

1393
01:38:14,208 --> 01:38:16,042
Since then we've been friends.

1394
01:38:16,125 --> 01:38:18,167
Rubbish!
- Sorry?

1395
01:38:18,167 --> 01:38:19,500
Rubbish... dirt in the barrel.

1396
01:38:26,500 --> 01:38:28,958
Don't guns frighten you, sir?

1397
01:38:30,417 --> 01:38:31,917
Are you holding the gun?

1398
01:38:34,292 --> 01:38:36,667
No, sir.
- Then what's to fear?

1399
01:38:38,333 --> 01:38:43,292
No, sir. I mean there are often
articles in newspapers...

1400
01:38:43,292 --> 01:38:47,708
'Man shoots himself with gun.'

1401
01:38:48,958 --> 01:38:53,792
Fear creeps in when the
barrel is pointed at you.

1402
01:38:53,792 --> 01:38:55,417
In the army...

1403
01:38:55,417 --> 01:39:04,500
Vinod! Inform Sheila that a
certain
Govind is here to see her.

1404
01:39:11,667 --> 01:39:12,958
What are you doing here?

1405
01:39:13,167 --> 01:39:14,458
Nothing, sir.

1406
01:39:14,458 --> 01:39:17,583
Why are you creeping up
on me? - No, sir.

1407
01:39:19,750 --> 01:39:21,042
Are you alright?

1408
01:39:21,042 --> 01:39:22,333
Yes.

1409
01:39:22,500 --> 01:39:24,208
Are you sure?
- Yes, sir.

1410
01:39:24,750 --> 01:39:26,083
Then what are you doing here?

1411
01:39:27,042 --> 01:39:28,333
Sir... view.

1412
01:39:28,333 --> 01:39:29,917
View?
- The garden.

1413
01:39:29,917 --> 01:39:32,583
What about the garden?
- Butterfly.

1414
01:39:32,583 --> 01:39:35,458
- Butterfly? You like
butterfly?
- Yes, sir.

1415
01:39:35,458 --> 01:39:39,542
Big one. - Yes. - Small one.
- Yes. - Red ones.

1416
01:39:39,542 --> 01:39:42,833
- All types sir.
- All types of butterflies.

1417
01:39:43,333 --> 01:39:44,792
You like butterflies?

1418
01:39:44,792 --> 01:39:48,375
I love...
- Butterflies... wow!

1419
01:39:48,375 --> 01:39:49,792
Hi...

1420
01:39:49,875 --> 01:39:53,458
Sheila, let's go, we're running
late. - Yes, come on.

1421
01:39:53,458 --> 01:39:54,792
Just a minute...

1422
01:39:55,792 --> 01:39:59,167
Is the coffee on a train or a
bus
that it will leave without you?

1423
01:39:59,167 --> 01:40:00,917
- No, sir.
- You will miss it?

1424
01:40:00,917 --> 01:40:02,375
Dad!
- Just a minute.

1425
01:40:02,375 --> 01:40:04,000
Sheila does everything
at her own time

1426
01:40:04,000 --> 01:40:05,250
We literally counted hours
before she was born.

1427
01:40:05,250 --> 01:40:07,000
She spent two years in
the second grade. - Okay, dad.

1428
01:40:07,000 --> 01:40:09,000
She will get married when
she thinks its time...

1429
01:40:09,000 --> 01:40:11,875
..it also takes a while
to understand people.

1430
01:40:12,500 --> 01:40:16,083
You get it? - Yes. - Do you
gamble?
- Sometimes sir.

1431
01:40:16,083 --> 01:40:17,833
Do you drink?
- Sometimes.

1432
01:40:17,833 --> 01:40:19,083
With guys?

1433
01:40:19,083 --> 01:40:22,833
Sometimes. - With guys?
- Oh no, no, sir!

1434
01:40:22,833 --> 01:40:24,417
I was married twice before.

1435
01:40:24,417 --> 01:40:26,375
To whom?
- To women.

1436
01:40:26,375 --> 01:40:28,750
Are you sure?
- Sir, you are welcome to check.

1437
01:40:28,750 --> 01:40:30,042
Are you sure?
- Yes, sir.

1438
01:40:30,583 --> 01:40:32,750
Yes, sir. I love everything
about nature, sir.

1439
01:40:32,750 --> 01:40:35,000
I just want to have coffee
with Sheila, sir.

1440
01:40:35,000 --> 01:40:36,667
Okay, dad, that's enough!
Stop giving him a hard time?

1441
01:40:36,667 --> 01:40:37,958
Okay. That's it.

1442
01:40:37,958 --> 01:40:39,792
I am giving him a hard time?
- Yes!

1443
01:40:39,792 --> 01:40:43,375
He has been married twice
and he loves butterflies! - No.
No.

1444
01:40:43,375 --> 01:40:45,167
I am not giving him hard time.

1445
01:40:45,167 --> 01:40:47,250
Do you understand? Yeah. Okay.

1446
01:40:47,250 --> 01:40:48,583
Let's go!

1447
01:40:48,833 --> 01:40:50,375
Nine o'clock back home.

1448
01:40:50,375 --> 01:40:53,750
I'll make it, sir.
- I mean Sheila. Bye.

1449
01:40:53,750 --> 01:40:57,417
Okay, that's it, dad.
Bye, see you later. Come on.

1450
01:40:57,417 --> 01:41:00,125
Hey... see you later.

1451
01:41:00,125 --> 01:41:02,125
Okay, right, sir.

1452
01:41:02,125 --> 01:41:06,458
Come on!

1453
01:41:11,292 --> 01:41:13,250
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

1454
01:41:13,708 --> 01:41:17,375
Your dad is quite
an interesting man. Nice.

1455
01:41:17,458 --> 01:41:21,250
I was just looked at my watch,
he
said we should be back by nine.

1456
01:41:21,250 --> 01:41:22,958
He said a lot of other things.

1457
01:41:23,333 --> 01:41:25,542
He said I do everything late.
- Right.

1458
01:41:25,542 --> 01:41:28,333
We'll be back late,
he'll understand.

1459
01:41:28,333 --> 01:41:31,500
- No, no... - Come on!.
- No. Really.

1460
01:41:32,958 --> 01:41:36,917
Oh, my God.
- Oh God! Butterflies!

1461
01:41:41,500 --> 01:41:44,167
It's too much pressure.

1462
01:41:44,167 --> 01:41:45,667
So when did they get back?

1463
01:41:45,667 --> 01:41:47,333
On the dot at nine.

1464
01:41:47,333 --> 01:41:50,750
This time Sheila finally gave
in.

1465
01:41:50,750 --> 01:41:56,250
It's amazing love makes
people do amazing things.

1466
01:41:56,417 --> 01:41:57,750
Yup.

1467
01:42:01,583 --> 01:42:03,667
11 o'clock tomorrow?

1468
01:42:03,667 --> 01:42:08,250
11? Oh, yeah. A tour of Bombay?
- Exactly!

1469
01:42:08,250 --> 01:42:12,958
Exciting. Alright, I'll see you.

1470
01:42:12,958 --> 01:42:14,750
Text me when you get home.

1471
01:42:15,333 --> 01:42:18,208
Jai, this is Bombay. Don't
worry.

1472
01:42:18,208 --> 01:42:19,542
Corrected again!

1473
01:42:21,083 --> 01:42:25,833
- Pink butterfly!
- Garden butterfly!

1474
01:42:44,000 --> 01:42:49,750
"We are awake as well as
asleep.
We are a bit lost."

1475
01:42:49,750 --> 01:42:55,625
"Lost in love. Love, love,
what is love?"

1476
01:42:55,625 --> 01:43:01,542
"We are awake as well as
asleep.
We are a bit lost."

1477
01:43:01,542 --> 01:43:07,250
"Lost in love. Love, love,
what is love?"

1478
01:43:07,250 --> 01:43:12,750
"The air is vibrant.
Conversations are fragrant."

1479
01:43:12,750 --> 01:43:17,333
"The weather is so warm."

1480
01:43:17,333 --> 01:43:23,042
"Why do we fall in love?"

1481
01:43:23,042 --> 01:43:28,792
"If you know, tell me. I don't
know."

1482
01:43:28,792 --> 01:43:34,958
"Why do we fall in love?"

1483
01:43:34,958 --> 01:43:42,208
"If you know, tell me.
I don't know."

1484
01:43:42,208 --> 01:43:49,125
"I don't know."

1485
01:43:49,125 --> 01:43:52,500
"Is this love?"

1486
01:43:54,333 --> 01:44:01,250
"Can you feel it?
Tell me. Love. Love."

1487
01:44:01,250 --> 01:44:06,542
Have you wondered why your
previous
two marriages ended in a divorce?

1488
01:44:08,167 --> 01:44:09,500
Okay.

1489
01:44:10,625 --> 01:44:17,667
Suchitra and
I were classmates.

1490
01:44:17,750 --> 01:44:21,875
Back then I was in a band...

1491
01:44:22,250 --> 01:44:24,542
I was big John Travolta fan.
- Really?

1492
01:44:24,542 --> 01:44:26,292
you know 'Saturday Night Fever.'

1493
01:44:26,667 --> 01:44:30,000
Oh, how did if he's your love.

1494
01:44:31,083 --> 01:44:34,083
Dad said the same thing when
he...

1495
01:44:34,083 --> 01:44:36,750
learnt that Suchitra
was a Christian.

1496
01:44:37,000 --> 01:44:42,125
There was a lot of drama and
we ran away from home.

1497
01:44:42,125 --> 01:44:46,458
Jai sneaked out with his
dad's car and drove us.

1498
01:44:46,458 --> 01:44:48,167
We got married in the church
as well as the temple.

1499
01:44:48,833 --> 01:44:52,292
I was 23 and madly in love.

1500
01:44:55,167 --> 01:44:56,500
Anyway...

1501
01:44:58,292 --> 01:44:59,625
Then?

1502
01:45:01,417 --> 01:45:05,417
then we turned 24

1503
01:45:05,417 --> 01:45:08,958
and started thinking like
adults.

1504
01:45:09,583 --> 01:45:12,792
We didn't work out. And she
left me.

1505
01:45:13,625 --> 01:45:20,917
After that I was quite low
and working for my dad.

1506
01:45:20,917 --> 01:45:23,250
My dad manufactured ball
bearings.

1507
01:45:23,542 --> 01:45:28,167
