02:03:34,083 --> 02:03:36,167
Ritu will die of envy!

1759
02:03:36,167 --> 02:03:41,500
Naina! I didn't know
you were this filmy.

1760
02:03:41,500 --> 02:03:44,500
I mean it's cute but --

1761
02:03:44,583 --> 02:03:46,583
Listen, of course I am filmy.

1762
02:03:46,583 --> 02:03:51,083
By the way, 99 percent girls
who
meet SRK react in a similar way.

1763
02:03:51,083 --> 02:03:53,542
Right.
- He's just so charming.

1764
02:03:53,542 --> 02:03:55,000
Don't wash the hand, by the way.

1765
02:03:55,000 --> 02:03:56,250
Of course, I'm not
going to wash the hand.

1766
02:03:56,250 --> 02:03:58,417
Listen, haven't you watched
DDLJ?

1767
02:03:58,417 --> 02:04:00,458
I have but it has been a while.

1768
02:04:00,458 --> 02:04:01,792
So what?

1769
02:04:01,792 --> 02:04:04,875
Nobody makes a love
story like Shahrukh Khan.

1770
02:04:04,875 --> 02:04:06,125
We're going to watch it right
now.

1771
02:04:06,125 --> 02:04:09,875
No, Naina... - I can't
watch DDLJ, I promise! Oh God!

1772
02:04:15,000 --> 02:04:17,333
What unexpected rain!

1773
02:04:17,333 --> 02:04:19,458
Seriously! I think my watch
stopped.

1774
02:04:26,875 --> 02:04:29,375
What is this? You made a mess
again?

1775
02:04:29,375 --> 02:04:31,458
What is this?
- Not really.

1776
02:04:32,333 --> 02:04:36,375
Really? Look at this!

1777
02:04:36,375 --> 02:04:37,750
Here take this towel.

1778
02:04:39,792 --> 02:04:41,125
Here.

1779
02:04:42,458 --> 02:04:45,083
Dry yourself before
you pour out your anger!

1780
02:04:50,375 --> 02:04:55,542
Look at this... it says Bura
[Bad] Kebabs, not Bara [Big].

1781
02:04:56,125 --> 02:04:57,583
You want jumping chicken?

1782
02:04:59,292 --> 02:05:00,667
No!

1783
02:05:01,083 --> 02:05:04,625
Take your pick...
there's Chinese, Indian...

1784
02:05:04,875 --> 02:05:06,250
Nothing exciting.

1785
02:05:06,792 --> 02:05:08,000
Now what?

1786
02:05:08,000 --> 02:05:10,958
Do you know how to make
the perfect Maggi noodles?

1787
02:05:12,375 --> 02:05:17,375
Heat water, add the noodles,
let it boil for two minutes.

1788
02:05:17,375 --> 02:05:19,292
That's obvious my friend.

1789
02:05:19,417 --> 02:05:23,792
You also add cheese..

1790
02:05:23,792 --> 02:05:29,208
..chilli and my special
ingredient.

1791
02:05:29,500 --> 02:05:30,958
Is that so?

1792
02:05:33,750 --> 02:05:40,500
Tell me Sheila... you are
beautiful,
intelligent, funny...

1793
02:05:40,500 --> 02:05:46,458
and you know how to make
the perfect Maggi noodles.

1794
02:05:48,208 --> 02:05:51,417
I don't get it... you
can get any guy you like.

1795
02:05:51,542 --> 02:05:57,542
So how is it that you
still aren't... married...

1796
02:05:57,542 --> 02:06:01,208
The marriage question!
I was waiting for it.

1797
02:06:01,917 --> 02:06:03,667
This I don't get...

1798
02:06:04,292 --> 02:06:06,042
I mean, as soon as a girl is
born..

1799
02:06:06,042 --> 02:06:08,250
..you start thinking
of getting her married

1800
02:06:08,250 --> 02:06:10,792
It doesn't matter whether it's
through an matchmaking website
or...

1801
02:06:10,792 --> 02:06:12,167
the nephew of a neighbour or
through a distant relative.

1802
02:06:12,167 --> 02:06:13,542
Get her married off so..

1803
02:06:13,542 --> 02:06:14,917
..the parents feel
they've fulfilled their task.

1804
02:06:15,542 --> 02:06:17,958
What's with everybody
wanting me to get married?

1805
02:06:18,875 --> 02:06:20,917
There's a lot more to life than
that.

1806
02:06:21,083 --> 02:06:24,583
You were married twice,
what did you get?

1807
02:06:25,042 --> 02:06:26,417
True!

1808
02:06:28,333 --> 02:06:30,125
Thank God I didn't
give in to the pressure.

1809
02:06:30,625 --> 02:06:32,000
My logic was simple.

1810
02:06:32,208 --> 02:06:39,208
When I'd meet someone who's
outlook was off center like
mine..

1811
02:06:39,208 --> 02:06:44,833
..I would, you know and
you know what, I was right.

1812
02:06:45,708 --> 02:06:47,375
Well, I'm very happy to meet
you.

1813
02:06:47,792 --> 02:06:50,625
Wait. The secret ingredient!

1814
02:06:50,875 --> 02:06:52,750
Fried noodles?
- That's right!

1815
02:06:52,750 --> 02:06:54,667
In 'Maggi'?
- Yes. Try it.

1816
02:07:02,583 --> 02:07:03,917
Oh my God!

1817
02:07:04,125 --> 02:07:06,083
This is so good, I
think I want to marry it!

1818
02:07:13,417 --> 02:07:16,042
Hi Jai...
- Hello Naina.

1819
02:07:16,125 --> 02:07:17,458
Oh shit!
- What?

1820
02:07:17,458 --> 02:07:19,750
Sorry, I'll call you back.

1821
02:07:19,750 --> 02:07:21,125
Okay.

1822
02:07:29,458 --> 02:07:32,333
Hi Jai...
- It's Gayatri, darling.

1823
02:07:32,333 --> 02:07:34,208
Who is this Jai you were
expecting?

1824
02:07:34,208 --> 02:07:37,208
Gayatri? When did you get back?

1825
02:07:37,458 --> 02:07:39,333
Don't tell me you're set to
make me an aunt in nine months!

1826
02:07:39,333 --> 02:07:42,167
Shut up! I'll become an
aunt after you get married.

1827
02:07:42,167 --> 02:07:45,042
So is it Arjun's friend Jai?

1828
02:07:46,375 --> 02:07:48,292
Oh my God, Arjun was right!

1829
02:07:49,250 --> 02:07:50,708
About what exactly?

1830
02:07:50,708 --> 02:07:54,333
Just that there was some
connection between you and Jai.

1831
02:07:54,958 --> 02:07:56,792
It's not like that, Gayatri.

1832
02:07:56,875 --> 02:07:58,833
But you can make it like that,
Naina.

1833
02:07:59,167 --> 02:08:00,917
Dhruv proposed to me, Gayatri.

1834
02:08:03,000 --> 02:08:04,375
You know Jai and me...

1835
02:08:06,042 --> 02:08:07,542
..maybe in another lifetime.

1836
02:08:09,083 --> 02:08:12,833
Anyway, you know... just a
second.

1837
02:08:13,458 --> 02:08:17,167
It's your life, honey. Think
about it.

1838
02:08:17,292 --> 02:08:19,292
You want me to talk to Arjun?

1839
02:08:19,292 --> 02:08:21,250
Gayatri, it's Dhruv.

1840
02:08:21,250 --> 02:08:23,167
- Hi. - Hi.

1841
02:08:23,667 --> 02:08:26,833
- I'll call you back. - Okay,
bye.

1842
02:08:28,417 --> 02:08:29,792
What are you doing here?

1843
02:08:30,000 --> 02:08:33,125
- May I come in? - Of course,
come in.

1844
02:08:33,125 --> 02:08:36,000
Seven days are more than enough
to fall in love with Singapore.

1845
02:08:36,583 --> 02:08:38,583
Got done with my work and came
back.

1846
02:08:38,583 --> 02:08:40,125
When I landed I remembered
that...

1847
02:08:40,125 --> 02:08:41,458
I had forgotten my key back at
home.

1848
02:08:41,625 --> 02:08:44,583
So I had to come. I
would have called you. But..

1849
02:08:45,083 --> 02:08:48,000
What the hell? Why is this dog
here?

1850
02:08:48,583 --> 02:08:51,667
It's not a dog, Dhruv, it's a
puppy.

1851
02:08:51,667 --> 02:08:53,250
His name is Lucky.

1852
02:08:53,250 --> 02:08:56,042
A puppy is also a dog.
Where did you get it?

1853
02:08:56,042 --> 02:08:58,917
On the street, she was alone.

1854
02:08:58,917 --> 02:09:00,667
And you brought it home.

1855
02:09:00,667 --> 02:09:02,750
Naina, I am sure he
has 200 infections.

1856
02:09:02,750 --> 02:09:04,500
She!!
- Alright, she!

1857
02:09:04,500 --> 02:09:05,792
You are over reacting, Dhruv.

1858
02:09:05,792 --> 02:09:08,000
I'm not over reacting,
you know my allergies.

1859
02:09:08,000 --> 02:09:10,000
I have to take a shower.

1860
02:09:13,542 --> 02:09:18,375
Fine, you take a shower
and I will go to the studio.

1861
02:09:18,375 --> 02:09:20,417
I'm taking Lucky along.

1862
02:09:20,417 --> 02:09:22,417
I'll see you in the
evening and we'll talk.

1863
02:09:22,417 --> 02:09:23,750
Yes.

1864
02:09:31,083 --> 02:09:33,333
- Hi Naina... - Hi Jai.

1865
02:09:33,542 --> 02:09:35,917
Can I leave Lucky with
you for a few hours?

1866
02:09:35,917 --> 02:09:37,792
- Sure. - Thank you.

1867
02:09:37,792 --> 02:09:39,042
Everything alright?

1868
02:09:39,042 --> 02:09:41,667
Yes, I'll call in the evening.

1869
02:09:41,667 --> 02:09:43,417
Okay?
- Okay. - Thanks. Bye. - Bye.

1870
02:09:44,833 --> 02:09:46,792
Lucky, today I want you
to prove lucky for me.

1871
02:09:47,500 --> 02:09:48,875
Come on. Let's go.

1872
02:10:33,833 --> 02:10:37,542
Lucky, be my lucky mascot today.

1873
02:10:37,542 --> 02:10:39,875
So you will ring the bell.

1874
02:10:47,125 --> 02:10:48,458
Jai?

1875
02:10:48,875 --> 02:10:50,208
Dhruv?

1876
02:10:51,542 --> 02:10:54,542
Lucky... with you?

1877
02:10:54,708 --> 02:10:56,500
Well, Naina...

1878
02:10:56,500 --> 02:10:59,708
Naina gets everyone
involved in her social service.

1879
02:10:59,708 --> 02:11:01,125
Anyway, come on in.

1880
02:11:04,292 --> 02:11:05,958
So, can I get you something to
drink?

1881
02:11:06,375 --> 02:11:08,750
Coffee, beer, Bacardi?

1882
02:11:09,750 --> 02:11:11,542
No, thanks, Dhruv. Thanks a lot.

1883
02:11:13,708 --> 02:11:16,250
Hey babe, guess who is here!

1884
02:11:16,833 --> 02:11:18,458
Jai is here with Lucky.

1885
02:11:19,792 --> 02:11:21,667
Hi Jai.
- Hi Naina.

1886
02:11:22,708 --> 02:11:25,417
Actually, sorry, I should've
called.

1887
02:11:25,417 --> 02:11:26,625
That's not a problem.

1888
02:11:26,625 --> 02:11:29,792
Give me a second, I'll be back.

1889
02:11:32,667 --> 02:11:37,167
She's a little frisky, but
don't worry, I've fed her.

1890
02:11:37,167 --> 02:11:39,125
Thank you.
- She should be fine.

1891
02:11:42,292 --> 02:11:44,333
I guess, I should leave.

1892
02:11:44,333 --> 02:11:45,542
You just got here.

1893
02:11:45,542 --> 02:11:50,458
Yes, but I came to Bombay on
business and now it's over.

1894
02:11:50,458 --> 02:11:52,458
I should prepare to return.

1895
02:11:52,458 --> 02:11:55,333
You know what, spend
the evening with us.

1896
02:11:55,333 --> 02:11:57,625
Naina, I forgot to
tell you earlier that

1897
02:11:57,625 --> 02:11:58,958
I've invited some of my friends
over.

1898
02:12:00,833 --> 02:12:03,583
Now what? - Now we have to
organise dinner and drinks.

1899
02:12:03,583 --> 02:12:05,500
Why don't you invite
some of your friends?

1900
02:12:05,667 --> 02:12:07,542
Jai, you must stay, it will be
fun.

1901
02:12:08,792 --> 02:12:11,667
Thanks, Dhruv, but I should
leave.

1902
02:12:11,667 --> 02:12:16,083
No problem.
- Naina, he's your friend, tell
him.

1903
02:12:18,125 --> 02:12:19,458
Please stay, Jai.

1904
02:12:23,500 --> 02:12:25,458
Come on, guys. Let's play.

1905
02:12:25,583 --> 02:12:27,750
Each team has two players.

1906
02:12:27,750 --> 02:12:29,375
One player has explain the word

1907
02:12:29,375 --> 02:12:31,542
written on the top of the card.

1908
02:12:31,542 --> 02:12:33,167
So that's simple.

1909
02:12:33,167 --> 02:12:35,667
No, not simple.

1910
02:12:35,667 --> 02:12:37,667
The five closest
words used to explain...

1911
02:12:37,667 --> 02:12:39,708
that word are at the
bottom of the card.

1912
02:12:39,708 --> 02:12:42,333
And you have to get your
partner guess that very word...

1913
02:12:42,333 --> 02:12:44,042
without using those five words.

1914
02:12:45,333 --> 02:12:46,583
Ready?

1915
02:12:46,583 --> 02:12:48,208
Wait. I'll explain.

1916
02:12:48,583 --> 02:12:51,625
Say the word on top is Ritu.

1917
02:12:51,625 --> 02:12:54,292
The five words below is will
be...

1918
02:12:54,500 --> 02:13:00,000
- irritating, child, ice cream..

1919
02:13:00,000 --> 02:13:04,500
..silly and gorgeous.

1920
02:13:05,208 --> 02:13:06,458
So smart, Dhruv.

1921
02:13:06,458 --> 02:13:07,833
Let's get started. Now come on!

1922
02:13:07,833 --> 02:13:11,000
Naina, I think you
should partner with Jai.

1923
02:13:11,417 --> 02:13:12,958
But Dhruv --

1924
02:13:12,958 --> 02:13:14,417
But he doesn't know anyone.

1925
02:13:14,500 --> 02:13:17,167
He only knows Lucky and he
can't play.

1926
02:13:17,542 --> 02:13:20,875
And Ritu and I will referee,
okay?

1927
02:13:21,208 --> 02:13:23,125
Okay.

1928
02:13:23,292 --> 02:13:25,833
Okay, come on quick. Hi... I'm
Jai.

1929
02:13:29,083 --> 02:13:31,542
Okay guys, your time to starts
now.

1930
02:13:31,542 --> 02:13:33,750
Okay, Riya...
when we were in school...

1931
02:13:33,750 --> 02:13:36,458
your teacher ask you to
do this but you couldn't.

1932
02:13:36,458 --> 02:13:37,708
Maths?

1933
02:13:37,708 --> 02:13:39,250
Something else, come on...

1934
02:13:39,250 --> 02:13:40,500
Science!

1935
02:13:40,500 --> 02:13:42,542
Add them altogether, more...

1936
02:13:42,542 --> 02:13:43,750
Studies.

1937
02:13:43,750 --> 02:13:44,958
Okay, on to the next card.

1938
02:13:44,958 --> 02:13:46,500
You have this for your
breakfast.

1939
02:13:46,500 --> 02:13:47,708
Cereal.

1940
02:13:47,708 --> 02:13:49,250
No, something else!

1941
02:13:50,583 --> 02:13:53,542
Eggs. - No, not eggs,
something else, come on.

1942
02:13:54,292 --> 02:13:55,708
Okay, Scotch.

1943
02:13:55,708 --> 02:14:00,583
Whiskey!
- Move out of alcohol. Scotch.

1944
02:14:02,333 --> 02:14:04,417
I don't know.
- Time is running out guys!

1945
02:14:04,500 --> 02:14:06,917
Come on, Riya!
- Next!

1946
02:14:08,667 --> 02:14:10,000
Taxi?

1947
02:14:10,375 --> 02:14:11,750
Luggage?

1948
02:14:12,375 --> 02:14:17,125
Bags... where we first met.

1949
02:14:17,125 --> 02:14:19,208
Bus stop... bus!

1950
02:14:19,208 --> 02:14:23,583
Right! Okay this is very simple.

1951
02:14:23,958 --> 02:14:28,792
I said yellow and you said
orange.

1952
02:14:29,625 --> 02:14:33,667
Decorations... wedding...
flowers!

1953
02:14:33,667 --> 02:14:40,833
Right! Okay, go down.

1954
02:14:40,833 --> 02:14:44,250
Boxes?
- Jai, emergency!

1955
02:14:44,250 --> 02:14:46,042
Hospital.
- I'm here, aren't I?

1956
02:14:46,708 --> 02:14:50,542
Art gallery!
- Right! Okay.

1957
02:14:55,167 --> 02:14:56,500
Was...

1958
02:14:58,000 --> 02:14:59,375
Father.

1959
02:14:59,750 --> 02:15:04,208
Times up! That's a strange
clue but amazingly played.

1960
02:15:04,208 --> 02:15:05,792
Wow.

1961
02:15:06,792 --> 02:15:10,000
Well played guys, the
others still can't believe it.

1962
02:15:10,000 --> 02:15:11,250
Naina, dessert?

1963
02:15:11,250 --> 02:15:15,292
Yes, I'll come.
- Jai, join me for a smoke?

1964
02:15:15,292 --> 02:15:16,917
Yes. Come on.

1965
02:15:17,375 --> 02:15:22,250
You know, investment
banking is very stressful and...

1966
02:15:22,250 --> 02:15:26,083
to take the right decision at
the
right time can be very difficult.

1967
02:15:26,292 --> 02:15:27,708
Just like life.

1968
02:15:28,833 --> 02:15:30,875
And that's how I got this
habit of social smoking.

1969
02:15:31,917 --> 02:15:38,708
I get it, Dhruv. Sometimes
even I do it, bad habit, bro.

1970
02:15:43,375 --> 02:15:44,708
Yeah, what do you do?

1971
02:15:45,208 --> 02:15:48,833
I'm in marketing.
- Family?

1972
02:15:50,000 --> 02:15:52,125
Just mom.

1973
02:15:53,292 --> 02:15:55,792
You aren't married, yet? I
mean..

1974
02:15:56,875 --> 02:15:58,417
Well, even you aren't married.

1975
02:15:58,792 --> 02:16:05,625
Yeah, I guess didn't get
the time. What's your excuse?

1976
02:16:05,625 --> 02:16:08,667
I guess, I didn't get the right
girl.

1977
02:16:08,917 --> 02:16:12,958
Dhruv... they're
leaving after dessert.

1978
02:16:14,000 --> 02:16:15,375
Is this right?

1979
02:16:16,417 --> 02:16:19,708
What?
- Dessert plan!

1980
02:16:19,833 --> 02:16:23,083
Yeah.
- We'll leave too and we'll
drop you.

1981
02:16:23,417 --> 02:16:24,625
Good idea.
- Yeah.

1982
02:16:24,625 --> 02:16:25,958
Let's go.

1983
02:16:38,833 --> 02:16:41,541
Alright, Jai. It was a
pleasure meeting you again.

1984
02:16:41,541 --> 02:16:43,124
Stay in touch.

1985
02:16:43,500 --> 02:16:45,708
Bye Dhruv, all the best.

1986
02:16:46,000 --> 02:16:50,250
"There is loneliness."

1987
02:16:50,250 --> 02:16:53,416
"I don't know why."

1988
02:16:53,416 --> 02:16:56,791
"Why this punishment?"

1989
02:16:56,791 --> 02:17:01,707
"Who knows?"

1990
02:17:02,333 --> 02:17:06,125
"Paths are lonely."

1991
02:17:06,125 --> 02:17:09,875
"Arms are lonely."

1992
02:17:09,875 --> 02:17:11,958
"Eyes are lonely."

1993
02:17:11,958 --> 02:17:19,250
"Why do we meet when we
have to lose each other?"

1994
02:17:19,250 --> 02:17:26,666
"When heart has to wither,
why does it blossom?"

1995
02:17:26,666 --> 02:17:34,041
"Why do we meet when we
have to lose each other?"

1996
02:17:34,041 --> 02:17:37,666
"When heart has to wither.."

1997
02:17:37,791 --> 02:17:40,666
So that was a fun party.

1998
02:17:40,666 --> 02:17:42,999
Thank God, you had the spare
keys.

1999
02:17:43,750 --> 02:17:48,791
Thank God! Alright, Dhruv, see
you.

2000
02:17:48,791 --> 02:17:55,166
Naina, hold on.
What have you decided?

2001
02:17:55,250 --> 02:17:56,500
About what?

2002
02:17:56,500 --> 02:18:00,208
Destination or local? Big or
small?

2003
02:18:00,208 --> 02:18:02,292
The type of wedding, my love?

2004
02:18:05,041 --> 02:18:09,291
You always wanted to have a
beach wedding, didn't you?

2005
02:18:09,375 --> 02:18:14,166
Yes. I knew it, you know me so
well.

2006
02:18:14,166 --> 02:18:15,832
Before I forget...

